  "market_context": "On the daily NQ chart, price rallied into a daily bearish fair value gap, respected it, and closed lower, establishing a bearish next-day bias with previous day low as a downside draw on liquidity.",
  "key_observation": "After price respected the daily FVG and the hourly chart displaced through up-close candles (CISD), the next session opened, swept equal highs at 9:30, then printed a 2-minute CISD allowing a short toward equal lows and -2 to -2.5 standard deviations.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the daily chart, identify the bearish fair value gap as the higher time frame PD array and draw on liquidity, noting price reached up into it, respected it, and closed down.",
    "Step 2: Drop to the hourly chart to confirm bias — observe price displacing and closing below a series of up-close candles after engaging the daily FVG, validating a change in state of delivery.",
    "Step 3: Project a standard deviation Fibonacci from the hourly manipulation high down to the CISD low, marking the -2 to -2.5 zone as the hourly target.",
    "Step 4: Next day, note price ranges and forms equal lows while sweeping an old high — a buy-side liquidity sweep that aligns with the bearish bias for a short opportunity.",
    "Step 5: Drop to the 2-minute chart around the 9:30 open and watch for the manipulation up, followed by a close below the up-close candles confirming a 2-minute CISD.",
    "Step 6: Enter short on the 2-minute CISD with stop above the manipulation high; project standard deviations from the 2-minute manipulation leg and set target at the equal lows (also overlapping with -2 to -2.5 and the hourly target).",
    "Step 7: Manage the trade as price displaces lower, tagging the -2 to -2.5, -4 to -4.5 levels and reaching the hourly target."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade reached target — price hit the -2 to -2.5 and -4 standard deviation levels and continued down to the hourly target / equal lows.",
  "lessons": "A clean top-down workflow stacks confluence: HTF PD array sets bias, CISD on an intermediate time frame confirms it, and an LTF CISD after a liquidity sweep delivers a low-risk entry into pre-projected standard deviation targets.",
